<item>
  <title>RStudio Environment Cleanup Guide</title>
  <link>https://ChrisEnv.github.io/chrisenv.github.io/content/blog/01-rstudio_cleanup_guide/RStudio_Cleanup_Guide.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>This guide provides detailed instructions for cleaning up your computing environment on both Mac and Windows to ensure a fresh setup for RStudio. Using package managers like Homebrew for Mac and Chocolatey for Windows makes the process streamlined and consistent.</p>
<section id="for-mac-users-using-homebrew" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="for-mac-users-using-homebrew">For Mac Users (Using Homebrew)</h2>
<section id="uninstall-rstudio" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="uninstall-rstudio"><strong>Uninstall RStudio</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Open Terminal.</p></li>
<li><p>Use Homebrew to uninstall RStudio:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="ex" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">brew</span> uninstall <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">--cask</span> rstudio</span></code></pre></div></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="remove-configuration-files" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="remove-configuration-files"><strong>Remove Configuration Files</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Delete RStudio settings and session data:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb2-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-rf</span> ~/.rstudio-desktop</span></code></pre></div></li>
<li><p>Remove RStudio’s saved application state:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb3" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb3-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-rf</span> ~/Library/Saved\ Application\ State/com.rstudio.desktop.savedState</span>
<span id="cb3-2"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-rf</span> ~/Library/Saved\ Application\ State/org.rstudio.RStudio.savedState</span></code></pre></div></li>
<li><p>Delete RStudio preferences:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb4" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb4-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> ~/Library/Preferences/com.rstudio.desktop.plist</span>
<span id="cb4-2"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> ~/Library/Preferences/org.rstudio.RStudio.plist</span></code></pre></div></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="optional-clean-r-and-r-packages" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="optional-clean-r-and-r-packages"><strong>Optional: Clean R and R Packages</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Uninstall R:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb5" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb5-1"><span class="ex" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">brew</span> uninstall r</span></code></pre></div></li>
<li><p>Manually delete any installed R packages:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb6" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb6-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-rf</span> ~/Library/R</span>
<span id="cb6-2"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">rm</span> <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-rf</span> /Library/Frameworks/R.framework</span></code></pre></div></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="empty-trash" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="empty-trash"><strong>Empty Trash</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Ensure all deleted files are permanently removed by emptying the Trash.</li>
</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section id="for-windows-users-using-chocolatey" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="for-windows-users-using-chocolatey">For Windows Users (Using Chocolatey)</h2>
<section id="uninstall-rstudio-1" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="uninstall-rstudio-1"><strong>Uninstall RStudio</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Open an administrative command prompt or PowerShell.</p></li>
<li><p>Use Chocolatey to uninstall RStudio:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb7" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode powershell code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode powershell"><span id="cb7-1">choco uninstall rstudio</span></code></pre></div></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="remove-configuration-files-1" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="remove-configuration-files-1"><strong>Remove Configuration Files</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Delete RStudio settings from the user directory and application data:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb8" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode powershell code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode powershell"><span id="cb8-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
