<item>
  <title>Embed JavaScript in Quarto</title>
  <link>https://ChrisEnv.github.io/chrisenv.github.io/content/blog/03-quarto_js/quarto_js.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>Today we are diving into the world of JavaScript and how to embed it in Quarto. JavaScript is a powerful language that can be used to create interactive elements on a webpage. In this example, we will create a 3D cube using JavaScript and embed it in a Quarto document.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb1-1">::: {.cube-container}</span>
<span id="cb1-2">&lt;div id="cube"&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-3">  &lt;div class="face front"&gt;quarto&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-4">  &lt;div class="face back"&gt;p2m&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-5">  &lt;div class="face right"&gt;water&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-6">  &lt;div class="face left"&gt;data&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-7">  &lt;div class="face top"&gt;simulation&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-8">  &lt;div class="face bottom"&gt;chrisenv&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-9">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-10">:::</span></code></pre></div>
<div class="cube-container">
<div id="cube">
<div class="face front">
quarto
</div>
<div class="face back">
p2m
</div>
<div class="face right">
water
</div>
<div class="face left">
data
</div>
<div class="face top">
simulation
</div>
<div class="face bottom">
chrisenv
</div>
</div>
</div>



